cs.SE, cs.HC, cs.PL, cs.SY, cs.CR

The paper discusses a monitoring solution for software running in the field, which falls under the category of software engineering (cs.SE). The solution aims to collect comprehensive runtime data without negatively affecting the user experience, which suggests a focus on human-computer interaction (cs.HC). The technique involves encoding knowledge as a finite state model, which relates to programming languages (cs.PL) and systems and control (cs.SY). Finally, the paper evaluates the technique's impact on system response time, which is relevant to computer systems and networking (cs.CR).
